<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Allegedly Helped Wife's Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A 75-year-old man has been charged with  
manslaughter for allegedly hanging a noose from a ceiling beam and 
leaving his ailing wife alone to commit suicide. 
</P>
<P>
	Peter Florio, 75, pleaded innocent Friday and was ordered held  
on $10,000 bail, said Sherry Hunter, spokeswoman for the Queens 
district attorney. If convicted, he could face up to 15 years in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
	``They were a very loving couple and now the family is dealing  
with a tragedy of immense proportion,'' said Florio's lawyer, John 
Halton. 
</P>
<P>
	Ann Florio, 70, was diagnosed with Parkinson's disease and heart  
problems earlier this year. Her husband told police that she had 
repeatedly asked for his help in committing suicide as her health 
deteriorated. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday night, Florio allegedly drilled a hole through a  
ceiling beam in their home. Investigators said he then ran the rope 
through it and left a slipknot noose dangling. He left the 
apartment Thursday morning, and returned that afternoon to find his 
wife dead, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Halton would not comment on the circumstances of Mrs. Florio's  
death. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
