<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Thomas Hits Career Homer No. 300 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- White Sox slugger Frank Thomas hit a solo  
homer into the left-field seats off Oakland starter Kevin Appier 
with one out in the sixth inning for his 300th career home run. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas becomes the 84th player in major league baseball history  
to record 300 home runs. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas also becomes the fifth active player to record at least  
300 homers, 1,000 RBI (1,031) and 1,000 walks (1,050). He joins San 
Francisco's Barry Bonds, Tampa Bay's Fred McGriff, St. Louis' Mark 
McGwire and Baltimore's Cal Ripken, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas has three career home runs and is batting .360  
(18-for-50) lifetime against Appier. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
