<HEADLINE> Tipper Fills Pastries at Wis. Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Tipper Gore assumed the duties of pastry chef,  
filling cream puffs during a visit to the Wisconsin State Fair. 
</P>
<P>
	Wisconsin Attorney General James Doyle introduced Gore as ``the  
next first lady'' during her visit to the fairgrounds in suburban 
West Allis. 
</P>
<P>
	``Y'all have a great, beautiful day, and I appreciate your warm  
welcome,'' she said Thursday before her stint in the 38-degree 
pastry room. 
</P>
<P>
	Gore seized the opportunity to promote a Patient Bill of Rights  
that would ensure medical coverage for depression and other mental 
illnesses. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
