<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-07 19:01:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Jets Sign Kick Returner Stone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- The New York Jets signed veteran kick  
returner and wide receiver Dwight Stone on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not released.  
</P>
<P>
	Stone played the last four seasons with the Carolina Panthers  
after spending eight seasons with the Pittsburgh Steelers. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot, 195-pound Stone has averaged just 13 receptions per  
seasons over his career, but has 99 career special teams tackles 
and a 20.2 average on kickoff returns. 
</P>
<P>
	The Jets waived rookie free agent receiver/kick returner Eddie  
Conti. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
