<DOCNO> APW19990807.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-07 19:25:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  500,000 Revelers Party in Zurich </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) -- Switzerland's sober financial capital  
throbbed to the beat of techno music Saturday as a half a million 
revelers flooded the streets for the annual Lake Parade. 
</P>
<P>
	The event, which started in 1991, is now one of Europe's best  
known parades. Thirty Love Mobiles -- or huge trailers crammed with 
dancers -- wound their way through the packed lakeside streets in 
the country's biggest open air party. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 100,000 fans traveled from neighboring Germany. Swiss  
Railways added 50 extra trains and transformed its main train 
station into a hall for dressing up. 
</P>
<P>
	Traditional bankers' suits were replaced by crazy costumes,  
including ``Millennium'' space outfits, male miniskirts and bikinis 
crafted from coconuts and aluminum foil. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said there were no serious problems.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990807.0015 </DOCNO>
