<DOCNO> APW19990807.0022 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-07 20:20:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fusion 2, MetroStars 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Saul Martinez scored his first two  
goals in Major League Soccer as the Miami Fusion won their first 
game since losing top scorer Diego Serna, beating the New York-New 
Jersey MetroStars 2-0 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars suffered their fourth consecutive shutout and now  
have gone 366 minutes since scoring, an MLS record. Their last goal 
came in a 3-2 loss to New England on July 4. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez scored in the opening minute of the second half and  
again in the 56th minute to become the first Fusion player this 
year to score more than once in a game. 
</P>
<P>
	Nelson Vargas and Welton each had two assists and Garth Lagerwey  
made four saves to notch his third shutout. 
</P>
<P>
	Their performance easily made up for the loss of Serna, out for  
the season after tearing his anterior cruciate ligament in last 
Sunday's 4-0 loss to Columbus. Serna was fourth in MLS with 10 
goals. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami (9-13) won for the fifth time in its past six games and  
moved into third place in the Eastern Conference. The MetroStars 
(5-15) have lost 11 of 12. 
</P>
<P>
	After a scoreless first half, Martinez entered as a substitute  
and immediately made an impact. He faked goalkeeper Mike Ammann to 
the ground, leaped over his defender and put the ball in the left 
corner of the open net. 
</P>
<P>
	It took just 10 minutes for Martinez to make the score 2-0.  
After taking a cross from Vargas, he weaved between two defenders 
and shot past Ammann. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez, 23, was discovered during an invitational tryout in  
February. The Honduras native had 13 goals and three assists in two 
years with the Long Island Rough Riders of the A-League. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
