<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Los Angeles 4, San Jose 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Zak Ibsen scored his first goal of the  
season in the 14th minute, and Los Angeles added three insurance 
goals in the second half as the Galaxy defeated San Jose 4-1 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ibsen scored his goal off a long pass from Paul Caliguiri.  
Caliguiri passed to Ibsen in the box for an easy shot on Clash 
goalkeeper Joe Cannon. Mauricio Cienfuegos also recorded an assist 
on the play and added two more in the match to bring his season 
total to a league-leading 13. 
</P>
<P>
	Cobi Jones, Cienfuegos and rookie Seth George scored in the  
second half for Los Angeles (13-8). 
</P>
<P>
	Midfielder Braeden Cloutier scored his first goal of the season  
for the Clash (11-10) in the 84th minute. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
