<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mike Ditka Buys La. Restaurant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Mike Ditka has spent the past two seasons  
trying to Ditka-ize the New Orleans Saints. Now, a restaurant is in 
for the same fate. 
</P>
<P>
	Mike's on the Avenue, where for the past decade chef Mike  
Fennelly mixed the flavors of the American Southwest and several 
Asian countries, was sold to a group headed by Ditka. 
</P>
<P>
	The new fare will feature the flavors of New Orleans with the  
steak-and-chop-house fare of Chicago. And, of course, there will be 
a new name: Mike Ditka's Restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Saints at training camp in La Crosse, Wis., Ditka  
wanted to talk about football, not food. He declined to discuss the 
restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
	``That's not football. Next,'' Ditka said.  
</P>
<P>
	Developers plan to have the restaurant open by midseason. What  
are the chances of rubbing shoulders with the coach? 
</P>
<P>
	``Don't expect to see me there,'' Ditka said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
