<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Banshee Breeze Wins $250K Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Banshee Breeze collared Beautiful  
Pleasure in the stretch and prevailed by a half-length in 
Saturday's $250,000 Go for Wand Handicap at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	As expected, Beautiful Pleasure went directly to the lead while  
Jerry Bailey, widest away from the gate, dropped Banshee Breeze 
over to the rail before reaching the first turn, and quickly moved 
her into contending position just behind the leader. Coming into 
the stretch, Banshee Breeze moved to engage Beautiful Pleasure, 
assumed a short lead and held gamely to the precarious advantage 
through the final furlong. 
</P>
<P>
	Beautiful Pleasure held for second, 8 3/4 lengths ahead of Heritage  
of Gold. 
</P>
<P>
	As in her return from a year's inactivity on July 9, Mossflower  
showed no semblance of her best form, finishing a non-threatening 
fourth in the field of five, beating only Diggins. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze, last year's 3-year-old filly champion, remained  
undefeated in four starts this year, all in graded stakes. She 
previously won the Fleur De Lis at Churchill Downs and the Apple 
Blossom and Rampart, both at Gulfstream Park. 
</P>
<P>
	``Twelve pounds is a lot of weight to give up. She's been a  
beautiful thing and training this kind of filly is not hard work; 
you just point her in the right direction,'' winning trainer Carl 
Nafzger said. 
</P>
<P>
	Banshee Breeze, high-weighted at 124 pounds, went 1 1/8 miles in  
1:49 4-5 on the fast track to earn $150,000 for Jayeff B Stables 
and James B. Tafel. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $3.30, $2.30 and $2.10. Beautiful Pleasure  
paid $2.90 and $2.10 and Heritage of Gold was worth $2.10. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
