<HEADLINE> Scorsese's Daughter Gets Star Turn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Dominica Cameron-Scorsese, the daughter of  
director Martin Scorsese, is making her onstage debut in a play 
written by her mother, Julia Cameron. 
</P>
<P>
	Cameron-Scorsese plays Dawn, an angry heroin user battling her  
parents and her addiction, in ``Four Roses'' at the Century City 
Playhouse here. It runs until Aug. 22. 
  	   	
