<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gas Leak Cause of Texas Hotel Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GRAPEVINE, Texas (AP) -- Investigators confirmed Saturday that a  
gas leak was to blame for a blast that ripped through a new hotel, 
seriously burning a man and injuring dozens with broken glass. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire Marshal Dick Ward said natural gas lines that supplied the  
hotel's swimming pool heater caused the Friday evening explosion at 
the Embassy Suites Outdoor World. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas E. Marcer, a subcontractor who was working on the heater  
when the blast occurred, remained in serious condition Saturday at 
Parkland Hospital in Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
	Marcer, interviewed by authorities Saturday in his hospital  
room, and another worker apparently didn't know there was gas in 
the line as they worked on it, Ward said. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is no negligence involved by either one of these  
technicians,'' the fire marshal said. ``They were doing their jobs 
properly.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ward said the gas was ignited either by an electrical pump or an  
ignitor system on the pool equipment. 
</P>
<P>
	The explosion blew through an exterior wall and a gift shop only  
three days after the hotel opened. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten people, including six children, were treated for minor  
injuries at nearby hospitals. About two dozen other people were 
treated by paramedics at the scene for cuts. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials said the 330-unit hotel, located near Dallas-Fort  
Worth International Airport, might reopen early next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
