<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Club Opens 'Oz' Conference in Pa. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) -- It may not have a yellow brick road, but  
Pennsylvania's capital has the spirit of Judy Garland and the 
``Wizard of Oz'' this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	About 150 people are expected for a three-day conference that  
started Friday and features appearances by two of the original 
Munchkins. 
</P>
<P>
	Though the conference, one of three regional meetings sponsored  
by the International Wizard of Oz Club, focuses on all aspects of 
the Oz legacy, the 60th anniversary of the film's release is 
prompting a special emphasis on the 1939 film. 
</P>
<P>
	The conference features an auction and sale of Oz memorabilia, a  
costume contest and a short story contest for writers inspired by 
the 40 books written in the Oz series from 1900 to 1963. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is much discussion about the contributions of the series  
to the nature of fantasy and interpretations of the books as 
discussions of quests for self-identity,'' said Peter Hanff, the 
club's president. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
