<HEADLINE> Hemingway Had Fun Down Under </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Two things made a big impression on Mariel  
Hemingway while she was in Australia shooting her latest TV movie: 
the scenery and the men. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a gallant attitude there that I find very appealing,''  
Hemingway told People magazine in its Aug. 16 issue. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought 'Wow. I'm surrounded by beautiful guys. I'm just way  
too married and way too old!''' 
</P>
<P>
	Hemingway, 37, is married to filmmaker Steve Crisman and has two  
children with him. 
</P>
<P>
	In ``First Daughter,'' Hemingway plays a Secret Service agent  
trying to save the president's daughter from kidnappers. The TBS 
movie is scheduled to air Aug. 15. 
  	   	
