<HEADLINE> Cuban Basketball Player Defects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) -- Basketball player Juan Leopoldo  
Vazquez defected from his team today at the Pan American Games and 
plans to seek asylum in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	Vazquez did not show up for Cuba's game in the morning, then  
turned up elsewhere in Winnipeg accompanied by Ninoska Perez, 
director of the Cuban American National Foundation. Perez said 
Vazquez is hiring a lawyer with the intention of defecting to the 
United States. 
</P>
<P>
	He also told the same thing to Univision TV Channel 23 in Miami,  
where the CANF is headquartered. 
</P>
<P>
	Vazquez would be the ninth member of the Cuban delegation to  
leave, and the seventh athlete. A softball coach and a journalist 
also left. 
  	   	
</P>
