<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Figures on the Aging in America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	America's aging population:  
</P>
<P>
	-- Over 65: 34.5 million in 1999, estimated to increase up to 90  
million by 2040. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Over 85: 4.1 million in 1999, estimated to increase up to 18  
million by 2050. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Half of women and one in three men who reach age 65 will spend  
some time in a nursing home. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Today about 1.5 million people live in 17,176 nursing homes.  
That could grow to more than 5 million by 2040. 
</P>
<P>
	(Sources: U.S. Census Bureau, American Association of Retired  
Persons, American Health Care Association.) 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
